{
  "texts": [
    "Besides, Baidoo-Anu and Ansah (2023) noted that ChatGPT, released in November 2022, gained rapid popularity for its advanced capabilities.",
    "This study assesses its educational benefits, like personalized learning and formative assessment support, while also noting limitations, such as misinformation and biases.",
    "Recommendations include collaborative efforts to enhance education with ChatGPT safely.",
    "Chan and Tsi (2023) also present a preprint that delves into specific topics concerning teachers, AI, and Higher Education.",
    "This study explores AI's role in higher education, finding that while AI may enhance teaching, human teachers remain irreplaceable due to qualities like critical thinking and emotions."
  ]
}